======================================================================
PART 3: THE 21 TRANSITIVE TRIPLES = H_forb_2
======================================================================
For ANY regular tournament on n=7:
  3-cycles = C(7,3) - n × C((n-1)/2, 2)
           = 35 - 7 × C(3,2)
           = 35 - 7 × 3
           = 35 - 21 = 14
  Transitive triples = 21 = H_forb_2

This is NOT a coincidence!
  21 = n × C((n-1)/2, 2) for n=7
     = 7 × C(3,2) = 7 × 3 = 21
     = C(7,2) = 21

In general for regular tournaments on n vertices (n odd):
  transitive triples = n × C((n-1)/2, 2)
  For n=3: 3 × C(1,2) = 0 (every triple is a 3-cycle!)
  For n=5: 5 × C(2,2) = 5
  For n=7: 7 × C(3,2) = 21
  For n=9: 9 × C(4,2) = 54

α₂ values among regular n=7 tournaments: [7, 10, 14]
So α₁=14 is constant but α₂ varies — the TOPOLOGY varies!

